Heat the oil in a 6-quart saucepot over medium-high heat. Add the beef and cook until well browned on all sides. Pour off any fat. Stir the gravy and barbecue sauce, if desired, in the saucepot and heat to a boil. Reduce the heat to low. Cover and cook for1 1/2 hours. Add the carrots to the saucepot. Cover and cook for 1 hour or until the beef is fork-tender. Serve the beef with the gravy.